ProtoResult:
. "Let $a, b\in\mathbf{Z}$ and $n,m\in\mathbf{N}$ such that 
   $\gcd(n,m)=1$. Then there exists $x\in\mathbf{Z}$ such that 
   \begin{align*} x&\equiv a\pmod{m},\\ x&\equiv b\pmod{n}. 
   \end{align*} Moreover $x$ is unique modulo $mn$."
